            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-69" n="69">I ne'er could endure my Talent to smother</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-70" n="70">I told you one Tale, I'll tell you another</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-71" n="71">A Joyner, to fasten a Saint in a Nitch</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-72" n="72">Bor'd a large Auger-Hole in the Image's Breech</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-73" n="73">But finding the Statue to make no Complaint</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-74" n="74">He would ne'er be convinc'd it was a true Saint</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-75" n="75">When the true Wood arrives, as he soon will no doubt</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-76" n="76">For that's but a Sham Wood <note place="foot">·the Effigies of M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Wood were frequently carried about \<hi rend="italics">word deleted</hi>\ in Procession &amp; Burnt.</note> they carry about</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-77" n="77">What Stuff he is made on, you quickly may find</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-78" n="78">If you make the same Trial, and bore him behind</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-79" n="79">I'll hold you a Groat, when you wimble his Bum</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-80" n="80">He'll bellow as loud as the De'il in a Drum</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-81" n="81">From me, I declare, you shall have no Denial</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-82" n="82">And there can be no harm in making a Trial</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-83" n="83">And, when to the Joy of your Hearts, he has Roar'd</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-84" n="84">You may shew him about for a new Groaning-Board</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-85" n="85">om.</l>
