            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-109" n="109"><lb/>Hear one Story more, and then I will stop</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-110" n="110">I Dreamt, Wood was told, he should Die by a Drop</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-111" n="111">So methought, he resolv'd no Liquor to taste</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-112" n="112">For fear the first Drop might as well be his last</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-113" n="113">But Dreams are like Oracles, 'tis hard to explain 'em</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-114" n="114">For it prov'd that he dy'd of a Drop at Killmainham,<note place="foot">·the Name of the Place of Execution.</note></l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-115" n="115">I wak'd with Delight, and not without Hope</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-116" n="116">Very soon to see Wood drop down from a Rope</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-117" n="117">How he, and how we, at each other should grin</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-118" n="118">'Tis Kindness to hold a Friend up by the Chin</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-119" n="119">But soft, says the Herald, I cannot agree</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-120" n="120">For Metal on Metal, is false Heraldry</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-121" n="121">Why that may be true, yet Wood upon Wood</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-360Y-line-122" n="122">I'll maintain with my Life, is Heraldry Good</l>
